Local hospitals, managed by regional authorities, are spread over the whole of Russian territory, but the most serious cases are, as things stand, then transferred to the central hospitals which are mainly in Moscow and in Russia's biggest cities.
The University of California, San Francisco has taken over a post-transplant clinic for kidney patients at Kaiser Permanente's San Francisco hospital, bringing to an end Kaiser's brief - and scandal-plagued - foray into the organ transplant business.
Two months later, Kaiser agreed to pay a $ 2-million fine to state HMO regulators and make a $ 3-million donation for organ donor outreach.
